Founded
1969


Headquarters
Pico House, 4 Dai Fu Street, Tai Po Industrial Estate, N.T., Hong Kong, China



Area served

Worldwide



Key people

Lawrence Chia (Chairman)


Services



Event marketing
Conference and exhibition management
Venue management
Interior and retail design
Visual identity
Themed environment and related business





Revenue
US$534 million (2016)


Total equity
US$407 million (2016)



Number of employees

Over 2,000 (2016)


Website
Pico.com


Pico Far East Holdings Limited is an event marketing company founded in 1969 by Chia Siong Lim,[1] was named Pico Art Studio. It Incorporated in Singapore as a private limited company delivering exhibition stand-building work. It was listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange under the name Pico Far East Holdings Limited,[2] the chairman of the group is Lawrence Chia.[1]



Contents


1 History
2 Stock exchange
3 Subsidiaries and affiliates
4 Awards

4.1 2017
4.2 2016
4.3 2015
4.4 2014


5 References



History[edit]
Pico was founded in 1969 and has grown into a global group of companies with over 2,000 staff in 40 offices located in major cities around the world. Pico is currently expanding further into China, and is building large operations and production facilities in Beijing and Shanghai called Pico Creative Centres.
The bulk of Pico's work has involved designing and building exhibition stands and managing and providing services at mega-events like World Expos or Olympic Games.[3] Since 2010, the company has expanded its scope to include brand strategy consultation and planning, using a methodology called Total Brand Activation. Pico has received a number of accolades for its performance, including being named one of Asia's top three event companies by CEI Asia.[4]
Stock exchange[edit]
Pico has been listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange (SEHK: 0752)[2] since 1992, and their associate Pico (Thailand) Public Company Limited has been listed on Thailand’s MAI (SET: PICO)[5] since 2004.
